$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Hexadecimal chu decimal-a kan chantir dawnin a hmasa ber atan hex number chu 16-in i then tur a ni a, hei hian base number a pe ang che. Step hnihna chu hex number digit tin chu 16-a then a, result ziak tur a ni. A tawp berah chuan number chhut chhuah tawh zawng zawng kha han belhkhawm rawh.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Entirnan, mi pakhatin 9F7A chu decimal-ah a chantir duh a nih chuan 9F7A chu 16-in a then hmasa ang a, chu chu 6051 nen a inang ang a, chutah chuan 6051 digit tin chu 16-in an sem ang a, chu chu 381 nen a inang a, a tawp berah chuan 381 + 381 + 381 chu a inang vek ang 1144. Chuvangin decimal-a 9F7A chu 1144 nen a inang a ni';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Engtin nge Decimal chu Hexadecimal ah i convert theih ang?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Decimal chu hexadecimal-a chantir hi thil awlsam tak a ni a, calculator emaw online converter emaw hmanga tih theih a ni. Number convert tur chuan 16 in then la, a bak chu la rawh. Chumi hnuah chuan he la awm hi hexadecimal digit nen a inmil ang. Entirnan, decimal number 234 i neih chuan 16-in then la, a bak chu la rawh: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Chuvangin, hexadecimal notation-ah chuan he number hi “E2” tiin kan ziak ang.';
