$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Decimal aiin Hexadecimal hman hian eng hlawkna nge a neih?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Hexadecimal, a nih loh leh base-16, system hi decimal system nena inmil property thenkhat entawn tura siam a ni. Phên dangin sawi ila, keini mihringte tana thil awlsam zawk siamsak tura siam a ni. Number 423 hian decimal system-a digit 10 awm lovin digit 16 a nei a. Hei hi a chhan chu hexadecimal hian 10 aiah symbol 16 base a hmang a, F hnuah chuan order chu 0 hmangin a intan leh a, chutiang chuan 15 kan thlen thlengin F tia noted a ni.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Hexadecimal encoding hian decimal system nena khaikhin chuan digit awm zat chu factor riat in a tihtlem a ni. Tin, hexadecimal number hian information density a nei a, chu chu decimal number aiin a let hnih zetin a sang zawk a ni. Chuti a nih chuan, engvangin nge he funky little numbering scheme hi zir hi i buaipui ang? A chhan chu i nun a ti awlsam thei a ni! Digital system emaw data transmission emaw hmanga hnathawh hian hex hman hian cryptic message emaw data stream emaw decode-naah hun leh chakna a humhim ang.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Hexadecimal aiin Decimal hman hian eng hlawkna nge a neih?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Binary coding chungchang sawi dawn chuan Hexadecimal hian digit 8 chu 2 ah a tihhniam avangin a efficient zawk a, chubakah Hex hian binary aiin information density nasa zawk leh number dikna sang zawk a pe bawk. Hei hi Hex hian binary ang chi pahnih chauh hmang lovin symbol 16 a hmang zawk vang a ni. Hetianga efficiency tihpun avang hian Hexadecimal hi computing leh digital electronics-a binary coding siamnaah bakah computer science application atan pawh hman a ni fo thin.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Tin, Hexadecimal hian decimal aiin hmun a luah tlem zawk bawk. Binary digit 8 ni lovin digit pahnih chauh a awm avangin Hex number hian number lian tak takte chu a tawi zawkin a entir a ni. Hei hi computer system hmanga hnathawhnaah a \angkai hle thei a, hmun tinah decimal point tam tak nei decimal code nena khaikhin chuan hex code type-naah tihsual a awm tlem zawk avangin!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Hexadecimal hmanga tarlan theih value hrang hrangte chu engzat nge ni?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Hexadecimal number chu decimal system-a digit 10 kan hman aia digit 16 hmangtu number a ni. He number system hi base-16 an ti a, kan hriat lar decimal system property te entawn turin min pui a ni. Hexadecimal-ah chuan digit tin hian power 16 a entir a, number 0 atanga 9 hian 1 atanga 10 thlenga power a entir a, A atanga F thlengin 11 atanga 15 power a entir thung.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Decimal-a ang bawkin Hexadecimal-a symbol 16 hman a nih hnuah number order chu zero-ah a intan leh thin. Chuvangin, hexadecimal 10 chu decimal 16 nen a inang a, hexadecimal 11 chu decimal 17 nen a inang bawk.';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Decimal?'] = 'Decimal hmanga tarlan theih value hrang hrangte chu engzat nge ni?';
