$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Mathematics leh computer science-ah chuan hexadecimal (base 16, emaw hex pawh ni bawk) hi positional numeral system a ni a, a radix, a nih loh leh base chu 16 a ni a, symbol hrang hrang sawm leh paruk a hmang a, a tam zawkah chuan symbol 0–9 hmangin value zero atanga nine, leh A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) te chu value sawm atanga sawm leh panga aiawh turin. Entirnan, hexadecimal number 2AF3 chu, decimal-ah chuan (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , emaw 10,995 emaw nen a inang a ni.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Hexadecimal digit tin hian binary digit (bits) pali (&quot;nibble&quot; an ti bawk) a entir a, hexadecimal notation hmanna ber chu computing leh digital electronics-a binary coded value mihringte tana remchang taka entir nan a ni. Entirnan, byte value hi 0 atanga 255 (decimal) inkar a ni thei a, mahse awlsam zawkin 00 atanga FF inkar hexadecimal digit pahnih anga tarlan theih a ni. Hexadecimal hi computer memory address entir nan pawh hman a ni tlangpui bawk.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex hi Hexadecimal tih tawi a ni a, base -16 structure atanga siam a ni a, computer-a instruction pek dan awlsam zawka siam nan hman a ni. He 16 symbols number system hi 8-bit binary number tihkhawtlai nan siam a ni a, chuvangin data chu computer-ah theihtawp chhuah lovin encode theih a ni. Hex digit hrang hrang pahnih hmangin imprint leh type theih a ni a, hex digit tin hian nibble emaw 4-bits format emaw a lantir thei bawk.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'He number system hian symbol 16 a hmang a, chungte chu 0-9 emaw AF emaw inkar a ni. 0–9 hian number 9 thleng a entir a, AF erawh chu numeric 10–15 hmangin a entir thung. Number system chi thum dang nena khaikhin chuan hexadecimal numeral system hi a hlawk ber nia ngaih a ni.';
